{
  "stem": "2684.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through soccer, I lived a life which made up for me what I lost in-- in my German trips.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What had happened to your family?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family was the most fortunate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I can say that I am one of the very, very rare Jew in the world whose family survived, every one of them-- my father's.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother's, they'd been persecuted and executed in a very early stage of the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But my father, because he was well-known, they established a squadron of forced labor guys and called a-- a squadron, which called the clothing squadron.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What was their job?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody knows.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only things they quartered themselves in the Hungarian-Jewish gymnasium-- which is not gymnasium in Hungarian terms.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's the high school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Gymnasium is in-- we called the high schooling gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And with him was my whole family, about 70 or 80 of them, and another 800 Jew amongst them-- opera singers, world-famous singers who sings in the Metropolitan after that, actors, actresses, all the what you would call intellectuals-- and they bought themselves six or seven SS as a guard.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's what I heard from my parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the SS were guarding that place right through the area in such a way that no Germans and no bloody Hungarian could go near the place.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They couldn't get in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my sister, my cousins, who are all here, they were all hiding there, and all 700 or 800 persons survived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after the war, they paid the SS, and they left, and my parents came out and started their living.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So in that respect, I can say I was the sole persecuted in my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
